analysis:
Sentiment analysis from last week (2025-08-06 to 2025-08-12) to today (2025-08-14):

**Positive Developments:**

*   JPMorgan's Crawford still sees value in owning bonds in the US (2025-08-06).
*   JPMorgan's Stephen Parker anticipates a growth recovery in 2026 (2025-08-07).
*   JPMorgan and Carter's were highlighted as Zacks Bull and Bear of the Day (2025-08-06).
*   Chase made rewards points worth more than cash, with instructions on how to turn them into crypto gold (2025-08-05).
*   A healthy 'tortoise' of an economy, according to JPMorgan's David Kelly (2025-08-04).
*   If $1,000 had been invested in JPMorgan Chase (JPM) 5 years ago, the return would be significant (2025-08-04).
*   Bets on Fed rate cuts are sweeping through the US bond market (2025-08-06).
*   JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM) filed Form 10-Q for the quarter ended June 30, 2025 (2025-08-05).
*   A bull case theory for JPMorgan Chase (JPM) is presented (2025-08-04).
*   JPMorgan and Bank of America shares slide as Trump says banks discriminated against him (2025-08-05).
*   Consider this Bank ETF before the Fed cuts rate this fall (2025-08-04).

**Negative Factors/Risks:**

*   Trump says JPMorgan, Bank of America refused his business (2025-08-05).
*   Trump warns of payback for 'bad' treatment, as JPMorgan and Bank of America stocks drop (2025-08-05).
*   The worst of the tariffs is still yet to come, says JPMorgan's Joyce Chang (2025-08-04).
*   Slowing labor demand will lead the Fed to deliver rate cuts later this year, according to JPMorgan's Kelsey Berro (2025-08-04).
*   OPEC+ signals next move is undecided as a tumultuous chapter ends (2025-08-04).
*   JPMorgan downgrades International Paper, expressing investor hopes for a 2027 look as too high (2025-08-05).
*   The debanking issue is back as Trump slams major lenders (2025-08-05).
*   Corporate America remains obsessed with stock buybacks (2025-08-05).
*   Figma's pursuit of long-term backers kept its IPO price in check (2025-08-04).
*   Slowing labor demand will lead the Fed to deliver rate cuts later this year, according to JPMorgan's Kelsey Berro (2025-08-04).

**Sentiment Outlook for Today (2025-08-14):**

Based on the provided sentiment values, the dominant sentiment for today is neutral.
